In [74]:
labels = n_data_pivot['math_score']
x = np.arange(len(labels))  
width = 0.45  

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
Male_rects = ax.bar(x - width/2, n_data_pivot['male'], width, label='M') # Add color here
Female_rects = ax.bar(x + width/2, n_data_pivot['female'], width, label='F')

ax.set_xlabel('Punteggio')
ax.set_ylabel('Numero maschi/femmine')
ax.set_title('Numero di maschi e femmine che hanno raggiunto il punteggio')

fig.set_size_inches(18.5, 10.5)
plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 15})
ax.legend()

def gen_label(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate('{}'.format(height),
                    xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
                    xytext=(0, 3),  
                    textcoords="offset points",
                    ha='center', va='bottom')


gen_label(Male_rects)
gen_label(Female_rects)

fig.tight_layout()
